        <h1>Anes-Days Saved Methodology</h1>
        
        <p>This document provides a high-level picture and detailed validation of the calculation methodology used by the smAIrtRx OR Optimizer to identify and measure Anesthesia Provider savings. The system uses a multi-path optimization model to ensure maximum resource recovery without compromising clinical safety.</p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
            <h2>Hard Savings Recovery</h2>
            <p>Anesthesia provider savings are categorized as <strong>Direct Labor Recovery (Hard Savings)</strong>. This represents "leakage" where professional labor is paid for but idle through OR elimination, FTE hours reduction, and schedule gap absorption.</p>
            <p>Total "Anes-Days Saved" is the aggregate of three distinct optimization methods. This explains why anesthesia staffing savings often exceed physical room savings, as the model identifies efficiency gains within individual schedules as well as across the facility.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Optimization Paths</h2>
        
        <div class="formula-card">
            <span class="formula-title">Method 1: OR Elimination (Direct Attribution)</span>
            <p>Identifies providers who worked <em>exclusively</em> in rooms that were consolidated or eliminated by the physical asset optimizer. If a physical OR footprint is closed, the dedicated labor for that footprint is recovered.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="formula-card">
            <span class="formula-title">Method 2: Hours Reduction (FTE Efficiency)</span>
            <p>Compares total system-wide anesthesia coverage hours (from first case start to last case end) before and after optimization. Savings are calculated in units of standard workday blocks.</p>
            <div class="math">(Initial Coverage Window - Optimized Coverage Window) / OR Capacity = Saved FTEs</div>
        </div>

        <div class="formula-card">
            <span class="formula-title">Method 3: Coverage Gap Analysis (Absorption)</span>
            <p>A high-precision algorithm evaluates if a provider's entire daily case load can be "absorbed" into the idle temporal gaps of other providers on the same day, ensuring zero overlaps.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Data Integrity & Safety</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Temporal Synchronization:</strong> All anesthesia demand is calculated using <code>Anesthesia_Start</code> and <code>Anesthesia_End</code> timestamps, ensuring clinical presence is accounted for.</li>
            <li><strong>Deduplication Logic:</strong> The system employs a subtraction model to ensure that a provider-day saved in Method 1 is not counted again in Methods 2 or 3, maintaining absolute financial integrity.</li>
            <li><strong>Labor Yield:</strong> Efficiency is further validated by the "Labor Yield" metric, which compares professional work minutes against total paid capacity across the resource pool.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Mathematical Proof Sample</h2>
        <p>Example of schedule absorption (Site-Day Analysis):</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Baseline:</strong> 12 Anesthesiologists assigned across 12 physical ORs.</li>
            <li><strong>Optimization:</strong> 2 ORs eliminated (Method 1: 2 Anes-Days Saved).</li>
            <li><strong>Window Compression:</strong> Site-wide coverage duration reduced by 480 minutes (Method 2: 1 Anes-Day Saved).</li>
            <li><strong>Absorption:</strong> 1 additional provider's load fully fit into gaps of others (Method 3: 1 Anes-Day Saved).</li>
            <li><strong>Result:</strong> <strong>4 Total Anes-Days Saved</strong></li>
        </ul>

